<Link id="l00397" /><CodeLine lineNumber="397"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00398" /><CodeLine lineNumber="398"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Splits the SCEV into two vectors of SCEVs representing the subscripts and</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00399" /><CodeLine lineNumber="399"><Highlight kind="comment">/// sizes of an array access. Returns the remainder of the delinearization that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00400" /><CodeLine lineNumber="400"><Highlight kind="comment">/// is the offset start of the array.  The SCEV-&gt;delinearize algorithm computes</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00401" /><CodeLine lineNumber="401"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the multiples of SCEV coefficients: that is a pattern matching of sub</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00402" /><CodeLine lineNumber="402"><Highlight kind="comment">/// expressions in the stride and base of a SCEV corresponding to the</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00403" /><CodeLine lineNumber="403"><Highlight kind="comment">/// computation of a GCD (greatest common divisor) of base and stride.  When</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00404" /><CodeLine lineNumber="404"><Highlight kind="comment">/// SCEV-&gt;delinearize fails, it returns the SCEV unchanged.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00405" /><CodeLine lineNumber="405"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00406" /><CodeLine lineNumber="406"><Highlight kind="comment">/// For example: when analyzing the memory access A&#91;i&#93;&#91;j&#93;&#91;k&#93; in this loop nest</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00407" /><CodeLine lineNumber="407"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00408" /><CodeLine lineNumber="408"><Highlight kind="comment">///  void foo(long n, long m, long o, double A&#91;n&#93;&#91;m&#93;&#91;o&#93;) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00409" /><CodeLine lineNumber="409"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00410" /><CodeLine lineNumber="410"><Highlight kind="comment">///    for (long i = 0; i &lt; n; i++)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00411" /><CodeLine lineNumber="411"><Highlight kind="comment">///      for (long j = 0; j &lt; m; j++)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00412" /><CodeLine lineNumber="412"><Highlight kind="comment">///        for (long k = 0; k &lt; o; k++)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00413" /><CodeLine lineNumber="413"><Highlight kind="comment">///          A&#91;i&#93;&#91;j&#93;&#91;k&#93; = 1.0;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00414" /><CodeLine lineNumber="414"><Highlight kind="comment">///  &#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00415" /><CodeLine lineNumber="415"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00416" /><CodeLine lineNumber="416"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the delinearization input is the following AddRec SCEV:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00417" /><CodeLine lineNumber="417"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00418" /><CodeLine lineNumber="418"><Highlight kind="comment">///  AddRec: &#123;&#123;&#123;%A,+,(8 &#42; %m &#42; %o)&#125;&lt;%for.i&gt;,+,(8 &#42; %o)&#125;&lt;%for.j&gt;,+,8&#125;&lt;%for.k&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00419" /><CodeLine lineNumber="419"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00420" /><CodeLine lineNumber="420"><Highlight kind="comment">/// From this SCEV, we are able to say that the base offset of the access is %A</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00421" /><CodeLine lineNumber="421"><Highlight kind="comment">/// because it appears as an offset that does not divide any of the strides in</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00422" /><CodeLine lineNumber="422"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the loops:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00423" /><CodeLine lineNumber="423"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00424" /><CodeLine lineNumber="424"><Highlight kind="comment">///  CHECK: Base offset: %A</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00425" /><CodeLine lineNumber="425"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00426" /><CodeLine lineNumber="426"><Highlight kind="comment">/// and then SCEV-&gt;delinearize determines the size of some of the dimensions of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00427" /><CodeLine lineNumber="427"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the array as these are the multiples by which the strides are happening:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00428" /><CodeLine lineNumber="428"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00429" /><CodeLine lineNumber="429"><Highlight kind="comment">///  CHECK: ArrayDecl&#91;UnknownSize&#93;&#91;%m&#93;&#91;%o&#93; with elements of sizeof(double)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00430" /><CodeLine lineNumber="430"><Highlight kind="comment">///  bytes.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00431" /><CodeLine lineNumber="431"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00432" /><CodeLine lineNumber="432"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Note that the outermost dimension remains of UnknownSize because there are</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00433" /><CodeLine lineNumber="433"><Highlight kind="comment">/// no strides that would help identifying the size of the last dimension: when</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00434" /><CodeLine lineNumber="434"><Highlight kind="comment">/// the array has been statically allocated, one could compute the size of that</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00435" /><CodeLine lineNumber="435"><Highlight kind="comment">/// dimension by dividing the overall size of the array by the size of the known</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00436" /><CodeLine lineNumber="436"><Highlight kind="comment">/// dimensions: %m &#42; %o &#42; 8</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00437" /><CodeLine lineNumber="437"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00438" /><CodeLine lineNumber="438"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Finally delinearize provides the access functions for the array reference</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00439" /><CodeLine lineNumber="439"><Highlight kind="comment">/// that does correspond to A&#91;i&#93;&#91;j&#93;&#91;k&#93; of the above C testcase:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00440" /><CodeLine lineNumber="440"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00441" /><CodeLine lineNumber="441"><Highlight kind="comment">///  CHECK: ArrayRef&#91;&#123;0,+,1&#125;&lt;%for.i&gt;&#93;&#91;&#123;0,+,1&#125;&lt;%for.j&gt;&#93;&#91;&#123;0,+,1&#125;&lt;%for.k&gt;&#93;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00442" /><CodeLine lineNumber="442"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00443" /><CodeLine lineNumber="443"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The testcases are checking the output of a function pass:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00444" /><CodeLine lineNumber="444"><Highlight kind="comment">/// DelinearizationPass that walks through all loads and stores of a function</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00445" /><CodeLine lineNumber="445"><Highlight kind="comment">/// asking for the SCEV of the memory access with respect to all enclosing</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00446" /><CodeLine lineNumber="446"><Highlight kind="comment">/// loops, calling SCEV-&gt;delinearize on that and printing the results.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00447" /><CodeLine lineNumber="447" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#abc378caf5071493fe3b2b98bf224be7c"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#abc378caf5071493fe3b2b98bf224be7c">llvm::delinearize</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scalarevolution">ScalarEvolution</a> &amp;SE, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/scev">SCEV</a> &#42;Expr,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00448" /><CodeLine lineNumber="448"><Highlight kind="normal">                       <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl&lt;const SCEV &#42;&gt;</a> &amp;Subscripts,</Highlight></CodeLine>
